<p class=3D"MsoListParagraph" style=3D"margin-left:1.0in">E.g. 608 instead =
of 608-1</p>
<ol style=3D"margin-top:0in" start=3D"5" type=3D"1">
<li class=3D"MsoListParagraph" style=3D"margin-left:0in;mso-list:l0 level1 =
lfo1">Hit the search button and the invoice will show up in a list below.
<ol style=3D"margin-top:0in" start=3D"1" type=3D"a">
<li class=3D"MsoListParagraph" style=3D"margin-left:0in;mso-list:l0 level2 =
lfo1">If you search by customer name, a list of all invoices for that custo=
mer will be there.</li></ol>
</li><li class=3D"MsoListParagraph" style=3D"margin-left:0in;mso-list:l0 le=
vel1 lfo1">After locating the invoice that you want to return, click on the=
 invoice number.
<ol style=3D"margin-top:0in" start=3D"1" type=3D"a">
<li class=3D"MsoListParagraph" style=3D"margin-left:0in;mso-list:l0 level2 =
lfo1">It will be blue</li></ol>
</li><li class=3D"MsoListParagraph" style=3D"margin-left:0in;mso-list:l0 le=
vel1 lfo1">You will be taken to the return screen.
<ol style=3D"margin-top:0in" start=3D"1" type=3D"a">
<li class=3D"MsoListParagraph" style=3D"margin-left:0in;mso-list:l0 level2 =
lfo1">Here you can view all items that are on the invoice. It works similar=
 to the cart where the top list is filled with items, and you =E2=80=9Cadd=
=E2=80=9D them to the return cart.
</li><li class=3D"MsoListParagraph" style=3D"margin-left:0in;mso-list:l0 le=
vel2 lfo1">Before you click
<i>Return Item</i>, note that it is defaulted to return the item at full pr=
ice. You can change that by entering the desired amount in the textbox unde=
r the header
<i>Amount to Refund</i> in the list.</li></ol>
</li><li class=3D"MsoListParagraph" style=3D"margin-left:0in;mso-list:l0 le=
vel1 lfo1">After the items that need to be returned are in the second list,=
 click
<i>Reimburse Customer</i> to be taken to the second part of the return proc=
ess.
<ol style=3D"margin-top:0in" start=3D"1" type=3D"a">
<li class=3D"MsoListParagraph" style=3D"margin-left:0in;mso-list:l0 level2 =
lfo1">If the customer changes their mind or you have put something that sho=
uldn=E2=80=99t be returned into the return cart, you can click on the blue =
text that reads
<i>Cancel Return </i>beside the item to take it off the return cart.</li></=
ol>
</li><li class=3D"MsoListParagraph" style=3D"margin-left:0in;mso-list:l0 le=
vel1 lfo1">Similar to the checkout screen, you can now select which method =
you want to use to refund the customer.
<ol style=3D"margin-top:0in" start=3D"1" type=3D"a">
<li class=3D"MsoListParagraph" style=3D"margin-left:0in;mso-list:l0 level2 =
lfo1">You can use multiple refund methods.</li><li class=3D"MsoListParagrap=
h" style=3D"margin-left:0in;mso-list:l0 level2 lfo1">If the refund method i=
s incorrect, you can remove it by clicking
<i>Remove Refund Method.</i></li></ol>
</li><li class=3D"MsoListParagraph" style=3D"margin-left:0in;mso-list:l0 le=
vel1 lfo1">Once the refund remaining refund is 0, you can process the refun=
d by clicking on
<i>Process Refund</i>.
<ol style=3D"margin-top:0in" start=3D"1" type=3D"a">
<li class=3D"MsoListParagraph" style=3D"margin-left:0in;mso-list:l0 level2 =
lfo1">Much like the sales process, you can return to the cart by clicking
<i>Return to Cart</i> to make any adjustments that you need.</li></ol>
</li></ol>
